The man appeared in court on Tuesday where the matter was remanded to 7 June. CAPE TOWN -  A child abuse case against a father who flung his one-year-old child off a roof in New Brighton has been postponed until next month. The man appeared in court on Tuesday where the matter was remanded to 7 June. He flung his daughter off the roof of his shack in a tense standoff with police in the Joe Slovo informal settlement last month, while resisting the demolition of his home. A metro police caught the child. (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)